    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-27T13:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-27T13:48:00-05:00" n="1130"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1130">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.2311/8–1852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1130fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_KDD1">Kennedy</persName> and cleared in the offices of
                            <persName corresp="#p_BBO1">Bryan</persName> (<gloss target="#t_SMSA1"
                            >S/MSA</gloss>), <gloss target="#t_OFD1">OFD</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_H1">H</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                        >NEA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-27T14:48:00-04:00"
                            >August 27, 1952—2:48 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>292. Suggest you express regret delay involved and inform <gloss target="#t_PM1"
                        >PM</gloss> US prepared extend 35 year, two and one-half percent loan for
                    $15 million to <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> for purchase wheat
                    (approximately 150,000 tons) in US as measure to assist <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> meet its critical need for food (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1402 May 20 <hi rend="italic">et seq</hi>.).<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1130fn2">Not printed.</note> General understanding covering loan
                    wld be discussed Wash and cld be taken care of by exchange <pb facs="0769"
                        n="1819" xml:id="pg_1819"/> letters between <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. Loan agreement and
                    note wld be signed with <gloss target="#t_EXIM1">Ex-Im</gloss> Bank. This not,
                    however, <gloss target="#t_EXIM1">Ex-Im</gloss> Bank loan since <gloss
                        target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> auth involved making possible much better
                    terms. World Bank official stated loan this character in his view wld not affect
                    Bank’s loans to <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> now contemplated, while
                        <gloss target="#t_EXIM1">Ex-Im</gloss> loan wld do so. This important
                    consideration and of course in <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>s interest in
                    pressing its econ development. <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> funds so
                    limited impossible get more than $15 million and it is hoped this much wheat
                    will do job per <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>’s comment in <gloss
                        target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> and purchases already made other sources.
                    Believe best raise question details understanding involved in Wash after
                    indication <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>’s willingness proceed. Suggest
                        <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> instruct its <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss> open discussions with <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                    >Dept</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Re <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>’s comment (penultimate para <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 230 Aug. 18)<note n="3" xml:id="d1130fn3"
                        >Not printed.</note> Spanish loan was under direct Congressional mandate
                    with specific reference in legis; UK loan made under special provision <gloss
                        target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> legis relating to general <gloss
                        target="#t_instrs1">instrs</gloss> to <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> to
                    extend ten percent of aid provided for in form of loan. Neither of these loans
                    made under <gloss target="#t_EXIM1">Ex-Im</gloss> auth and policies.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> to use at ur discretion strenuous effort
                    involved not only in <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> but in various
                    agencies to arrive this conclusion which explains time taken. Hope <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> understands that US has made very great effort
                    to help under difficult circumstances.</p>
                <p>Vital there be no publicity this matter until understanding reached on details
                    and you advised. Pls inform <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> re this.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
